{{nihongo|'''Uda Mikumari Shrine'''|宇太水分神社|Uda Mikumari-jinja|}} is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|Shinto shrine|WD=Q845945|lt=Shinto shrine|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|Uda, Nara|en|Uda, Nara|WD=Q863747|lt=Uda|1=Uda, Nara}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|en|Nara Prefecture|WD=Q131287|lt=Nara|1=Nara Prefecture}}, {{ill|Japan|en|Japan|WD=Q17|lt=Japan|1=Japan}}. It is dedicated to ''{{ill|mikumari|WD=Q11129547|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/mikumari|qq=|1=Mikumari}}'', a female [[Shinto]] [[kami]] associated with water. The ''[[honden]]'' was built near the end of the {{ill|Kamakura period|en|Kamakura period|WD=Q236205|lt=Kamakura period|1=Kamakura period}}, and is listed as a {{ill|List of National Treasures of Japan (shrines)|en|List of National Treasures of Japan (shrines)|WD=Q3245520|lt=National Treasure of Japan|1=List of National Treasures of Japan (shrines)}}.
